parameters.name: RADIAL_DIST
parameters.description: The distance of the spacecraft from Mercury.

parameters.name: MSO_LOCAL_TIME
parameters.description: The Mercury longitude of the spacecraft.

parameters.name: MSO_LATITUDE
parameters.description: The Mercury latitude of the spacecraft.

parameters.name: MSGR_MSO_X
parameters.description: The X position of the spacecraft in the MSO frame.

parameters.name: MSGR_MSO_Y
parameters.description: The Y position of the spacecraft in the MSO frame.

parameters.name: MSGR_MSO_Z
parameters.description: The Z position of the spacecraft in the MSO frame.

parameters.name: RAW_ENERGY
parameters.description: The Energy of the particle event. (Peak -  Baseline)

parameters.name: ENERGY
parameters.description: The calibrated energy of the particle.

parameters.name: ENERGY_PEAK
parameters.description: PHA value corresponding to the particle energy.

parameters.name: ENERGY_BASELINE
parameters.description:
Baseline against which the particle energy is
 measured.

parameters.name: ION_E_FLAG
parameters.description:
Identifies event as either electron or ion. 0 -
 electron; 1 - ion.

parameters.name: EPHEMERIS_TIME
parameters.description:
Solar System Barycentric event time in the J2000
 system.

parameters.name: FRACTIONAL_YEAR
parameters.description:
Solar System Barycentric event time in the J2000
 system.

parameters.name: DAY_OF_YEAR
parameters.description:
Solar System Barycentric event time in the J2000
 system.

parameters.name: INTEGRATION_TIME
parameters.description: Integration/Accumulation time in seconds.

parameters.name: ENERGY_BIN
parameters.description:
High resolution energy bin number computed by the flight
 software. 
   (0-35); Unavailable, =99, before FSW6

parameters.name: MULTIPLE_HITS
parameters.description:
Flag indicating if more than one detector received a
 hit. (0 - 1, 99 for Low Energy Ion PHA)

parameters.name: CHANNEL_NUM
parameters.description:
Indicates the high energy ion or electron channel.
 (99 for Low Energy Ion PHA)

parameters.name: PRIORITY_GROUP
parameters.description:
Priority group of the event. (1-7) Only relevant prior
 to FSW6.

parameters.name: RATE_WEIGHT
parameters.description:
Weight to normalize PHA events to rate channels. 
   (Only relevant prior to FSW6, after FSW6, = 99)
